commit_message: changed which file is shown as workflow
updated workflow and add script and env
added rule to preprocess initial bam files if they were created with bwa mem -M; separated rule to compute PCA from plotting
added option to pre-split bam reads before smoove call. (in case mapping was done with bwa meme -M
added variable for number of chrs necessary for plink
changed way of saving pca pdf
removed processes number from smoove genotype
changed how to add population to PCA
tip on how to define sample name for the sample list file
added instructions on how to install r packages
replaced population line where sample name in file needed to completely match name in vcf. now the start of the sample name from the file should match the sample name in the VCF
added mamba to the environment requirements
updated PCA plotting to include population info
added rule to create final tsv file
add rule to create two vcfs - one with DUP, INV and DEL, which also contains the depth. One for BNDs with no depth
updated additional intro, set up and results sections
added step to install vep cache
sample list is now a two column csv. Read the sample names from the first column
added survivor env for SV stats
added rule to compute simple statistics like number of deletions, etc
added VEP env, duphold and pca script
added rules for running smoove. rule to check if outdir is defined
